The paper introduces a new large-scale, open-domain Chinese machine reading comprehension (MRC) dataset, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models and neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions a shared competition to encourage the exploration of more models, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
